    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean if the long term result was a power vacuum and more extremism, doesn't that make the whole idea of \"humanitarian intervention\" kind of a flawed concept? like, if you can't guarantee stability, is it even ethical or strategic to go in and topple a government just because you don't like the leader? it seems like it just trades one problem for a much worse one.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
